AWS_CLI installation steps

sudo apt-get install python3
sudo apt update
sudo apt install python3-pip
Following this link: (https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/install-linux.html)
$ pip3 install awscli --upgrade --user

download data to local folder 
wget url 
For other wget options e.g. to restore a paused download https://www.howtoforge.com/linux-basics-how-to-download-files-on-the-shell-with-wget 

Enable S3 permissions for your instance through policies.
https://github.com/churchlab/millstone/wiki/Moving-Data-Between-S3-and-EC2-Instances
